-- Insolvent Heiligendamm Hotel Gets Six Potential Bids, Welt Says
-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 2012-03-09T07:15:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-09/insolvent-heiligendamm-hotel-gets-six-potential-bids-welt-says.html
Grand Hotel Heiligendamm, the German
luxury hotel used for the Group of Eight meeting in 2007, has
received offers or inquiries from six serious bidders following
its insolvency filing last month,  Welt newspaper  reported today,
citing an interview with insolvency administrator Joerg Zumbaum.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
 nmagnusson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
